        dc:source  "PMID:17996703" .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "\"To test if our purified TFIIH and pol II were transcriptionally active, we first combined both epitope-tagged multiprotein complexes with bacterially expressed recombinant (r) human TFIIB, rTBP, rTFIIE, rTFIIF, a supercoiled DNA template (pG5MLT, which contains five Gal4-binding sites preceding the adenovirus major late core promoter elements), and a linearized DNA template (pMLΔ53, which contains the adenovirus major late core promoter elements without the Gal4-binding sites). As shown in Fig.5 A, both immunoaffinity-purified pol II complexes were equally active in transcribing the DNA templates, in conjunction with f:TFIIH, purified from the ammonium sulfate fraction, and other GTFs (comparelane 1 with lane 10).\" PMID:9852112" ;
  lego:evidence          :5ae3b0f600000054 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2018-05-01" ;
  pav:providedBy         "http://www.wormbase.org" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:RO_0002333 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :5323da180000008 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/#5323da1800000002%2F5595c4cb00000117>
] .

obo:BFO_0000051  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

lego:iuphar_id  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

skos:note  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "\"To investigate whether they could support human RNAPII ubiquitylation in vitro, highly purified human RNAPII was used as substrate, with human Uba1 and UbcH7 (or UbcH5C) involved as E1 and E2, respectively (Figure 6C, lanes 7–10). In this highly purified, reconstituted human RNAPII ubiquitylation system (see Figure S4 for purity of these proteins), Nedd4 (and Smurf1), but none of the other Rsp5 homologs, supported robust ubiquitylation of RNAPII (Figure 6C, lanes 2 and 3).\" PMID:17996703" , "\"Several independent experiments showed that UV-induced ubiquitylation was reproducibly affected only by Nedd4 siRNA (Figure 5C, compare lane 4 with lane 14 [control] and other knockdowns; data not shown). This indicates that Nedd4 is required for UV-induced ubiquitylation of RNAPII in vivo.\" PMID:17996703" , "\"Dramatically reduced UV-dependent ubiquitylation was indeed observed in the stable Nedd4 knockdown cells compared to wild-type cells immediately after UV irradiation, but after 20 min, the level of ubiquitylation in the two cell lines was already similar, as expected (Figure 5D, compare lanes 5 and 6, and 7 and 8).\" PMID:17996703" ;
  lego:evidence          :5ae3b0f600000039 , :5ae3b0f600000042 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2018-05-01" ;
  pav:providedBy         "http://www.wormbase.org" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:RO_0002333 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :5323da180000003 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/#5323da1800000002%2F5595c4cb00000122>
] .

